<!-- ─── 7 Reasons Atheer Is Different ─── -->
<section id="why-atheer" style="background: #0A0F1C;">
  <div class="section-inner reveal">
    <div class="section-label">Why Atheer</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">7 Reasons Atheer Is Different</h2>
    <p class="section-desc section-desc-wide">
      Every mobile inference engine runs LLMs. Here&rsquo;s why Atheer is the only one built for the NPU era &mdash; with predictive thermal management, hierarchical memory, structured output, and autonomous agents, all in safe Rust.
    </p>
    <div class="features-grid" id="reasons-grid">

      <div class="feature-card reveal">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-blue">⚡</div>
        <h3>#1 &mdash; NPU-First Multi-Backend</h3>
        <p>Atheer auto-probes NPU &rarr; GPU &rarr; CPU on both iOS and Android &mdash; CoreML/ANE, Metal, NNAPI, Vulkan &mdash; and selects the fastest available accelerator. Per-operation routing even sends decode to CPU in Eco mode to conserve GPU memory.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:#64748B;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">Competitors don&rsquo;t:</strong> No other engine probes NPU before GPU before CPU on both platforms. llama.cpp has no NPU path. MLC LLM has none. ExecuTorch has Qualcomm-only. MLX Swift has none.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card reveal">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-cyan">▦</div>
        <h3>#2 &mdash; Predictive Thermal Orchestration</h3>
        <p>Least-squares regression on live 1&thinsp;Hz telemetry predicts temperature trajectory and pre-emptively downgrades inference mode <em>before</em> the OS thermal throttle hits &mdash; replacing the sudden 60% performance cliff with graceful degradation.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:#64748B;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">Competitors don&rsquo;t:</strong> No mobile inference engine has thermal-aware operation. Every competitor runs flat-out until the OS forcibly throttles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card reveal">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-amber">⊞</div>
        <h3>#3 &mdash; L1/L2/L3 KV Cache Hierarchy</h3>
        <p>A three-tier cache with promotion scoring and explicit handoff protocols. L1 holds the active session, L2 retains recent sessions for fast recall, and L3 stores compressed/archived context &mdash; designed for multi-turn agent sessions on memory-constrained devices.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:#64748B;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">Competitors don&rsquo;t:</strong> Every other engine uses a single flat KV cache with no tiering, no promotion, and no cross-session handoff.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card reveal">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-green">◆</div>
        <h3>#4 &mdash; Grammar-Constrained Decoding</h3>
        <p>A first-class <code>GrammarConstraint</code> trait implements a pushdown automaton that guarantees valid JSON output at every decode step &mdash; not a post-processing bolt-on, but a native part of the generation loop with thread-safe <code>Send + Sync</code> semantics.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:#64748B;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">Competitors don&rsquo;t:</strong> Only llama.cpp has comparable GBNF grammar support, but it&rsquo;s a C API bolt-on, not a first-class trait in a safe language.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card reveal">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-purple">⟳</div>
        <h3>#5 &mdash; Built-in Agent Loop</h3>
        <p>An autonomous <code>Agent</code> struct with configurable <code>max_steps</code> handles the generate &rarr; parse &rarr; tool-call &rarr; continue cycle natively. No need to build orchestration logic in the host app &mdash; Atheer ships the loop.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:#64748B;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">Competitors don&rsquo;t:</strong> Every other mobile engine is a text-in-text-out API. You must build agent orchestration, context management, and tool-calling yourself.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card reveal">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-pink">◉</div>
        <h3>#6 &mdash; UniFFI Cross-Platform Bindings</h3>
        <p>One UniFFI definition generates idiomatic Swift packages for iOS and Kotlin packages for Android &mdash; from the same Rust codebase, with no platform-specific wrapper code or duplicate SDK maintenance.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:#64748B;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">Competitors don&rsquo;t:</strong> llama.cpp exposes a raw C API requiring per-platform wrappers. ExecuTorch is C++-only. MLX Swift is Apple-exclusive.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card reveal">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-blue">◈</div>
        <h3>#7 &mdash; Safe Rust, Not C/C++</h3>
        <p>Rust&rsquo;s ownership model guarantees no use-after-free, no data races, and no GC pauses. <code>catch_unwind</code> wraps ANE forward calls so accelerator panics don&rsquo;t crash the host app. Memory safety at the FFI boundary, zero-cost abstractions everywhere.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.8rem;color:#64748B;"><strong style="color:#F59E0B;">Competitors don&rsquo;t:</strong> Most mobile inference engines are written in C/C++ with manual memory management. Only MLX Swift shares Rust&rsquo;s safety guarantees &mdash; but it&rsquo;s Apple-only.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── Features ─── -->
<section id="features">
  <div class="section-inner reveal">
    <div class="section-label">Features</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Designed for on-device AI</h2>
    <p class="section-desc section-desc-wide">
      Atheer combines hardware-accelerated inference with agentic capabilities — all in safe Rust, all running locally on mobile. Every feature maps to actual code in the workspace.
    </p>
    <div class="features-grid">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-blue">⚡</div>
        <h3>Multi-Backend GPU/NPU</h3>
        <p>Metal (iOS GPU via Candle), custom GLSL compute shaders compiled via <strong>naga</strong> for Android Vulkan, raw NDK FFI bindings for NNAPI (NPU/DSP), CoreML ANE compatibility detection — automatic probe with graceful CPU fallback via <code>atheer-accel</code>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-cyan">◆</div>
        <h3>Structured Output</h3>
        <p>Character-level grammar-constrained decoding via a 38-state Pushdown Automaton in <code>atheer-orchestrator/src/grammar/</code> — guarantees valid JSON at every token, zero external dependencies, no post-processing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-amber">⟳</div>
        <h3>Agentic Workflows</h3>
        <p>Built-in speculative decoding (NGram cache), tool-calling definitions with JsonGrammar integration, and autonomous agent loops — bring your own tools via the <code>Agent</code> trait in <code>atheer-orchestrator</code>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-green">▦</div>
        <h3>Adaptive Mode Switching</h3>
        <p>Turbo / Balanced / Eco modes switch in real-time using a predictive moving-average thermal model with trend detection — 1 Hz hardware telemetry from <code>atheer-hardware</code> feeds the <code>Orchestrator</code> for preemptive downgrades.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-purple">⊞</div>
        <h3>Memory Hierarchy</h3>
        <p>L1/L2/L3 KV cache with INT8/INT4 quantization and adaptive depth by context length. PagedAttention block manager (16-token blocks) eliminates fragmentation. Incremental checkpoint deltas enable sub-100ms save/restore.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon feature-icon-pink">◉</div>
        <h3>Performance-per-Watt</h3>
        <p>Criterion microbenchmarks (model-free) + <code>perf-bench</code> binary with model-dependent suites for throughput, latency, checkpoint, memory, energy, and thermal throttling. All in <code>perf-bench/</code> and <code>tests/benches/</code>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── Architecture ─── -->
<section id="architecture" style="background: #0A0F1C;">
  <div class="section-inner reveal">
    <div class="section-label">Architecture</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Stack from silicon to inference</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">A layered architecture across 7 Rust crates — hardware telemetry flows up, acceleration dispatches down, and the orchestrator ties them together.</p>
    <div class="arch-grid">
      <div class="arch-card l1"><h4>iOS / Android App</h4><p>Swift · Kotlin · uniffi FFI</p></div>
      <div class="arch-card l2"><h4>atheer-ffi</h4><p>uniffi-generated bindings with streaming callback support</p></div>
      <div class="arch-card l2"><h4>atheer-core</h4><p>Candle inference · session mgmt · KV quantizer · lifecycle</p></div>
      <div class="arch-card l3"><h4>atheer-accel</h4><p>Metal · Vulkan (custom GLSL) · NNAPI NDK FFI · CoreML · CPU</p></div>
      <div class="arch-card l3"><h4>atheer-orchestrator</h4><p>Predictive mode selection · PDA grammar sampler · agent loop</p></div>
      <div class="arch-card l3"><h4>atheer-memory-bank</h4><p>L1/L2/L3 KV cache · PagedAttention blocks · handoff protocol</p></div>
      <div class="arch-card l3"><h4>atheer-hardware</h4><p>1 Hz telemetry · Android JNI bridge · iOS objc2 FFI</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-row">
      <span class="arch-pill">⟳ 1 Hz health → mode selection</span>
      <span class="arch-pill">⚡ Metal / Vulkan compute shaders</span>
      <span class="arch-pill">⊞ NNAPI NDK FFI (9 ops)</span>
      <span class="arch-pill">▦ Character-level PDA grammar</span>
      <span class="arch-pill">◉ PagedAttention 16-token blocks</span>
      <span class="arch-pill">◆ INT8/INT4 KV cache quant</span>
    </div>
    <p style="text-align:center;margin-top:1.5rem;font-size:.8rem;color:#475569;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">
      atheer-hardware ─1 Hz→ orchestrator ─mode→ atheer-core ─tensor→ atheer-accel
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── Backend Support ─── -->
<section id="backends">
  <div class="section-inner reveal">
    <div class="section-label">Platform Support</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">iOS &amp; Android, every accelerator</h2>
    <p class="section-desc section-desc-wide">
      Atheer auto-probes the best available backend in platform-specific priority order. NPU → GPU → CPU. 
      Each backend is implemented as a Rust crate module — no black boxes.
    </p>
    <div class="backend-grid">
      <div class="backend-card">
        <div class="backend-platform">iOS — Priority 1</div>
        <h4>CoreML / ANE</h4>
        <p>Apple Neural Engine via <code>candle-coreml</code> integration. <code>ANECompatibility</code> struct with per-layer heuristics, model size ceiling, and quantization whitelist. Falls back to Metal for incompatible architectures. <code>catch_unwind</code> protected.</p>
        <span class="backend-priority">ANE detection · macOS build</span>
      </div>
      <div class="backend-card">
        <div class="backend-platform">iOS — Priority 2</div>
        <h4>Metal GPU</h4>
        <p>GPU acceleration via <code>candle_core::Device::Metal</code>. Full tensor ops for prefill and decode in <code>atheer-accel/src/metal.rs</code>.</p>
        <span class="backend-priority">iOS 15+ · Candle Metal backend</span>
      </div>
      <div class="backend-card">
        <div class="backend-platform">Android — Priority 1</div>
        <h4>NNAPI NPU/DSP</h4>
        <p>Raw NDK FFI bindings with ~20 extern functions covering device discovery, graph construction (9 ops), compilation, and execution. Full pipeline in <code>atheer-accel/src/nnapi_ndk.rs</code>.</p>
        <span class="backend-priority">API 24+ · NDK r29+</span>
      </div>
      <div class="backend-card">
        <div class="backend-platform">Android — Priority 2</div>
        <h4>Vulkan GPU</h4>
        <p>Custom GLSL compute shaders (gemv.glsl, attention.glsl) compiled to SPIR-V via <code>naga</code> at build time. DP4A-style int8 matrix-vector multiply and flash attention in <code>atheer-accel/src/vulkan.rs</code> (~1120 lines).</p>
        <span class="backend-priority">API 26+ · custom compute shaders</span>
      </div>
      <div class="backend-card">
        <div class="backend-platform">Fallback</div>
        <h4>CPU</h4>
        <p>Always available fallback using Candle CPU backend. Graceful degradation when no accelerator is available — graceful, tested, documented.</p>
        <span class="backend-priority">Any platform · zero acceleration</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── Quick Start ─── -->
<section id="quickstart" style="background: #0A0F1C;">
  <div class="section-inner reveal">
    <div class="section-label">Quick Start</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">From zero to inference</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Build the workspace, run tests, and integrate into your iOS or Android app.</p>
    <div class="code-block-wrap">
      <div class="code-header">
        <span>bash</span>
        <button class="code-copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <pre class="code-block"><code><span class="comment"># Build the entire workspace</span>
cargo build --workspace

<span class="comment"># Run all ~390 tests</span>
cargo test --workspace

<span class="comment"># Download a test model (~350 MB)</span>
scripts/download-test-model.sh

<span class="comment"># Run integration tests with a real model</span>
ATHEER_TEST_MODEL=./models/LFM2-700M-Q4_0.gguf \
  cargo test -p atheer-core -- --ignored

<span class="comment"># Benchmark throughput</span>
cargo run -p perf-bench -- \
  --model-path model.gguf \
  --batch-sizes 1,4,8</code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="code-block-wrap" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <div class="code-header"><span>swift</span><span style="font-size:.7rem;color:#475569;">iOS integration</span></div>
      <pre class="code-block"><code><span class="keyword">import</span> <span class="type">AtheerFFI</span>

<span class="keyword">var</span> config = <span class="type">AtheerConfig</span>()
config.modelPath = <span class="string">"/models/llama.gguf"</span>
config.adaptive = <span class="keyword">true</span>

<span class="keyword">let</span> engine = <span class="type">AtheerEngine</span>(config: config)
<span class="keyword">try</span> engine.initialize()

<span class="keyword">var</span> request = <span class="type">GenerationRequest</span>(prompt: <span class="string">"Hello"</span>)
<span class="keyword">let</span> response = <span class="keyword">try</span> engine.generateSync(request: request)
<span class="built_in">print</span>(response.text)</code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="code-block-wrap" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <div class="code-header"><span>kotlin</span><span style="font-size:.7rem;color:#475569;">Android integration</span></div>
      <pre class="code-block"><code><span class="keyword">import</span> uniffi.atheer_ffi.*

<span class="keyword">val</span> config = <span class="type">AtheerConfig</span>(
    modelPath = <span class="string">"/models/llama.gguf"</span>,
    modelId = <span class="keyword">null</span>,
    draftModelPath = <span class="keyword">null</span>,
    adaptive = <span class="keyword">true</span>,
    maxTokens = <span class="number">2048u</span>,
    temperature = <span class="number">0.7f</span>,
    quantization = <span class="string">"q4_0"</span>,
    adaptiveHandoff = <span class="keyword">true</span>,
    memoryBankSizeMb = <span class="number">256u</span>,
    standbyDraftPath = <span class="keyword">null</span>
)

<span class="keyword">val</span> engine = <span class="type">AtheerEngine</span>(config)
engine.initialize()

<span class="keyword">val</span> request = <span class="type">GenerationRequest</span>(
    prompt = <span class="string">"Hello"</span>,
    maxTokens = <span class="number">512u</span>,
    temperature = <span class="number">0.7f</span>
)
<span class="keyword">val</span> response = engine.generateSync(request)
<span class="built_in">println</span>(response.text)</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── Benchmarks ─── -->
<section id="benchmarks">
  <div class="section-inner reveal">
    <div class="section-label">Benchmarks</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Benchmarking infrastructure</h2>
    <p class="section-desc section-desc-wide">
      Atheer ships with Criterion microbenchmarks and a dedicated <code>perf-bench</code> binary for measuring throughput, energy, and thermal behavior. No fabricated numbers — results depend on your device and model.
    </p>
    <div class="bench-grid">
      <div class="bench-card">
        <h4>Criterion Bench Harnesses</h4>
        <div class="bench-cat">atheer-benches (model-free)</div>
        <div class="bench-row">
          <div class="bench-label"><span>kv_cache bench</span><span>read/write/evict latency</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="bench-row">
          <div class="bench-label"><span>ngram_cache bench</span><span>match/miss throughput</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="bench-row">
          <div class="bench-label"><span>orchestrator bench</span><span>mode switch overhead</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bench-card">
        <h4>perf-bench Binary</h4>
        <div class="bench-cat">model-dependent suites</div>
        <div class="bench-row">
          <div class="bench-label"><span>--batch-sizes 1,4,8</span><span>throughput scan</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="bench-row">
          <div class="bench-label"><span>--duration-secs 300</span><span>sustained thermal</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="bench-row">
          <div class="bench-label"><span>JSON report output</span><span>per-batch samples</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bench-card">
        <h4>What gets measured</h4>
        <div class="bench-cat">per commit / per release</div>
        <div class="bench-row">
          <div class="bench-label"><span>Token throughput</span><span>tok/s (prefill + decode)</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="bench-row">
          <div class="bench-label"><span>Thermal throttling</span><span>mode degradation curve</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="bench-row">
          <div class="bench-label"><span>Energy per token</span><span>power draw samples</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── Roadmap ─── -->
<section id="roadmap" class="roadmap-wrap">
  <div class="section-inner reveal">
    <div class="section-label">Roadmap</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">What&rsquo;s Next</h2>
    <p class="section-desc section-desc-wide">
      Atheer is shipping incrementally. Here&rsquo;s what&rsquo;s built, what&rsquo;s in progress,
      and what&rsquo;s planned for the next milestones.
    </p>
    <div class="roadmap-grid">

      <div class="phase-card">
        <div class="phase-header">
          <div class="phase-icon phase-icon-lock">🔒</div>
          <div class="phase-title-group">
            <div class="phase-title">Security &amp; Reliability</div>
            <span class="phase-timeline">2–3 weeks</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul class="phase-list">
          <li class="phase-item done"><span class="status-icon">✅</span> PII redactor infinite loop fix</li>
          <li class="phase-item in-progress"><span class="status-icon">🟡</span> Fix 14 test failures &amp; 40+ warnings</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Model signature verification (Ed25519)</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Hash verification at model load time</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> GGUF format validation</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Encrypt L2/L3 cache at rest</li>
          <li class="phase-item in-progress"><span class="status-icon">🟡</span> CI env var fix + macOS runner</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-card">
        <div class="phase-header">
          <div class="phase-icon phase-icon-shield">🔐</div>
          <div class="phase-title-group">
            <div class="phase-title">Privacy Hardening</div>
            <span class="phase-timeline">2–3 weeks</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul class="phase-list">
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> AES-256-GCM for cache / checkpoints</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Secure memory wiping with <code>zeroize</code></li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Time-based cache expiry with secure deletion</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Audit logging</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> <code>delete_all_user_data()</code> API</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-card">
        <div class="phase-header">
          <div class="phase-icon phase-icon-bolt">⚡</div>
          <div class="phase-title-group">
            <div class="phase-title">Performance Validation</div>
            <span class="phase-timeline">2–3 weeks</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul class="phase-list">
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Real benchmarks &amp; populate BENCHMARKS.md</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Competitive benchmarks vs llama.cpp, MLC LLM</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Mode switching benchmark (wire orchestrator)</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Grammar overhead benchmark suite</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-card">
        <div class="phase-header">
          <div class="phase-icon phase-icon-globe">🌍</div>
          <div class="phase-title-group">
            <div class="phase-title">Market Readiness</div>
            <span class="phase-timeline">4–6 weeks</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul class="phase-list">
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Fix binding generation pipeline</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> GDPR compliance documentation</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Reference iOS and Android apps</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> Structured metrics / telemetry</li>
          <li class="phase-item planned"><span class="status-icon">🔵</span> API versioning for FFI layer</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
    <div class="roadmap-cta-row">
      <p class="roadmap-note">390+ tests <strong>→</strong> targeting 0 failures</p>
      <a href="https://github.com/achmadk/atheer-rust/blob/main/improvement_analysis.md" class="btn btn-secondary">View full improvement analysis →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─── Footer ─── -->
<footer>
  <div class="footer-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="footer-brand">Atheer-Rust</div>
      <p class="footer-desc">Mobile inference engine for LLMs on iOS and Android. Built with Rust, Candle, and a lot of type safety.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-links">
      <div class="footer-col">
        <h5>Docs</h5>
        <a href="#quickstart">Quick Start</a>
        <a href="#architecture">Architecture</a>
        <a href="#backends">Backends</a>
